	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101977284657528><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>Weight Factor</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=143963><span id= >fangdox</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>5 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Apr 25th 6:20 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>How do you monks make any pp?&nbsp;&nbsp;I mean, with my druid I used to sit and camp Gornit for 4-6 hours at a pop... ending up with 1k pp easily even after destroying all cp, sp, and weapons.  Even on a lower scale, killing orges in TD that drop fine steel weapons at level 20 or so.  With my druid I'd just take 6 bags with me and be able to fill them up in a few hours with weapons that are worth 3-5 pp each.  A nice 100 - 200 pp for a level 20 character.  I guess I could resort to just camping with my druid and handing the pp to my monk, but I'd rather get exp with my monk and bring him up as I did with my druid.<br><br>Am I missing the obvious answer or am I thinking straight, that I just have to deal with the weight and never plan on carrying anything with me other than what I'm using?  It's not a huge deal and I'll keep playing with my monkey (uhh.. nevermind), but if anyone has any feedback, feel free to post. Thanks.<br><br>Xcellence - 19th Monk of Luclin<br>Fangdox - 51st Druid of Luclin<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
